The code below powers a dashboard and issues 201 database queries when there are 200 open orders: one to load the orders and one per order to load its customer's name (a lazy @ManyToOne). Refactor it so the endpoint issues a constant, small number of queries regardless of how many orders exist, and state exactly how the query count changes. Provide at least the JOIN FETCH fix; a projection variant earns bonus credit.

// BEFORE
List<Order> orders = orderRepo.findAllByStatus(Status.OPEN);
List<Row> rows = new ArrayList<>();
for (Order o : orders) {
    rows.add(new Row(o.getId(), o.getCustomer().getName()));
}

